<subSubSection type="nomenclature">
<paragraph pageId="36" pageNumber="37">
<taxonomicName authority="Willmann, 1920" authorityName="Willmann" authorityYear="1920" class="Arachnida" family="Euphthiracaridae" genus="Pseudotritia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Oribatida" pageId="36" pageNumber="37" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="punctulata">Pseudotritia punctulata</taxonomicName>
(Berlese, 1913)
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection type="reference_group">
<paragraph pageId="36" pageNumber="37">
<taxonomicName authority="Berlese, 1904" authorityName="Berlese" authorityYear="1904" class="Arachnida" family="Phthiracaridae" genus="Phtiracarus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Oribatida" pageId="36" pageNumber="37" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="punctulatus">Phtiracarus punctulatus Berlese</taxonomicName>
, 1913, p. 102, pl. 8 fig. 97 2).
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="36" pageNumber="37">
<taxonomicName class="Gastropoda" family="Nassariidae" genus="Tritia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neogastropoda" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="punctulata">Tritia punctulata</taxonomicName>
, Lombardini, 1936, p. 50.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection type="discussion">
<paragraph pageId="36" pageNumber="37">
In 1913 Berlese used &quot; 
<taxonomicName authority="Berlese, 1904" authorityName="Berlese" authorityYear="1904" class="Arachnida" family="Phthiracaridae" genus="Phtiracarus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Oribatida" pageId="36" pageNumber="37" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Phtiracarus</taxonomicName>
&quot; instead of 
<taxonomicName class="Gastropoda" family="Nassariidae" genus="Tritia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neogastropoda" pageId="36" pageNumber="37" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">Tritia</taxonomicName>
; Berlese (1913a, p. 55) lists 
<taxonomicName authority="Berlese, 1904" authorityName="Berlese" authorityYear="1904" class="Arachnida" family="Phthiracaridae" genus="Phtiracarus" genus.completionEvidence="missing, matching species" genus.innerRound="1" genus.outerRound="1" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Oribatida" pageId="36" pageNumber="37" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="punctulatus">punctulatus</taxonomicName>
indeed as a &quot; 
<taxonomicName authority="Berlese, 1904" authorityName="Berlese" authorityYear="1904" class="Arachnida" family="Phthiracaridae" genus="Phtiracarus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Oribatida" pageId="36" pageNumber="37" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Phtiracarus</taxonomicName>
&quot; with other 
<taxonomicName class="Arachnida" family="Oribotritiidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Sarcoptiformes" pageId="36" pageNumber="37" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Oribotritiidae</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName class="Arachnida" family="Euphthiracaridae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Sarcoptiformes" pageId="36" pageNumber="37" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Euphthiracaridae</taxonomicName>
. The present species apparently belongs to the last-mentioned family. I have contributed it to the genus 
<taxonomicName authority="Willmann, 1920" authorityName="Willmann" authorityYear="1920" class="Arachnida" family="Euphthiracaridae" genus="Pseudotritia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Oribatida" pageId="36" pageNumber="37" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Pseudotritia</taxonomicName>
, although there is no certainty about this relationship.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="36" pageNumber="37">
The species was mentioned by Lombardini, but I have seen no slide in the 
<pageBreakToken pageId="37" pageNumber="38" start="start">Berlese</pageBreakToken>
Collection. Judging from the original description and figure the species mainly differs from 
<taxonomicName authority="Willmann, 1920" authorityName="Willmann" authorityYear="1920" class="Arachnida" family="Euphthiracaridae" genus="Pseudotritia" genus.bestMatchDistance="147" genus.bestMatchVote="2" genus.innerRound="1" genus.outerRound="1" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Oribatida" pageId="36" pageNumber="37" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="reticulata">P. reticulata</taxonomicName>
by the microsculpture of the tegument. The type-locality is &quot;Cansiglio&quot;.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="37" pageNumber="38">
2) Although fig. 97a, representing the microsculpture of a tegument, is placed close to fig. 97, it appears to belongs to fig. 98 (
<taxonomicName authority="Willmann, 1920" authorityName="Willmann" authorityYear="1920" class="Arachnida" family="Euphthiracaridae" genus="Pseudotritia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Oribatida" pageId="37" pageNumber="38" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="reticulata">Pseudotritia reticulata</taxonomicName>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
